  "title": "HR Manager (Manufacturing/Payroll, East)",
  "description": "<p>Responsibilities:</p>\n<ul>\n  <li><strong>Compensation &amp; Benefits:</strong></li>\n  <li>Ensure compliance with legal regulations (MOM, RBA) and HQ requirements.</li>\n  <li>Benchmark compensation with manufacturing/contract manufacturing/semicon industries.</li>\n  <li>Oversee yearly merit increment and appraisal process.</li>\n  <li>Propose salary adjustments for promotions and upgrades.</li>\n  <li>Plan and execute bonus payouts as per guidelines and budget.</li>\n  <li>Drive and participate in annual budgeting exercises.</li>\n  <li>Stay updated on market trends and regulatory changes.</li>\n  <li>Develop and maintain HR procedures and documentation.</li>\n  <li>Liaise with HRI and HRMC.</li>\n  <li>Implement continuous improvement initiatives and HR projects.</li>\n  <li><strong>Training &amp; Development:</strong></li>\n  <li>Guide HR Administrator on training-related matters.</li>\n  <li>Oversee employee training for skill and career development.</li>\n  <li>Conduct training needs analysis using the competency model.</li>\n  <li>Source and recommend suitable training programs.</li>\n  <li>Act as an internal consultant for learning and development initiatives.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Requirements:</p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Degree in HR Management or equivalent.</li>\n  <li>At least 5 years of managerial experience, ideally in manufacturing.</li>\n  <li>In-depth understanding of Singapore employment laws, HR best practices, C&amp;B analysis, and training functions.</li>\n  <li>Experience with Responsible Business Alliance (RBA) is an advantage.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>______________________________________________________</strong></p>\n<p><strong>HOW TO APPLY :</strong></p>\n<p><strong>Interested candidates, please submit your resume by clicking on “Quick Apply” or contact win@hkmsvs.com for more details.</strong></p>\n<p><strong>Please provide following information in the resume for immediate processing</strong></p>\n<p><strong>1) Reasons for leaving current and/or last employment</strong></p>\n<p><strong>2) Last drawn and/or current salary</strong></p>\n<p><strong>3) Expected salary</strong></p>\n<p><strong>4) Date of availability and/or Notice Period</strong></p>\n<p><strong>All applications will be treated in strictest confidence and only shortlisted candidates will be notified</strong></p>\n<p><strong>Wee Wai Dan</strong></p>\n<p><strong>EA License No : 03C5391</strong></p>\n<p><strong>EA Reg No : R22109628</strong></p>",
